Summer is thankfully here☀️ 
BUT please remember that drowning deaths in young children are preventable. It is so important that we actively supervise our children around water. Eyes on. Hands on. For more than 25 years, Keep Watch has been advising Australian parents and carers on how to keep their children safe when in, on or around the water. Keep Watch is aimed at preventing children aged 0 to 4 years from drowning by getting parents and carers to undertake four simple actions: supervise, restrict, teach and respond. Because ‘Kids can’t help themselves around water, you need to. @royallifesaving #keepwatch #drowningprevention #watersafety #ad

Lazy Saturday in my @ugg_express_australia ugg boots 💫 
 I am excited to be apart of the third annual Wear Your Uggs Day, which is proudly presented by Australian shoe manufacturer, Ugg Express and for this year’s campaign the brand is supporting a cause very close to their hearts, the national Christian charity Mission Australia. 

Wear Your Uggs Day was designed to encourage Australians to wear their ugg boots to work, school, or even at home, and by wearing your ugg boots on the first day of winter you’ll be able to help aid Mission Australia in their incredible work helping those experiencing homelessness in Australia. 

The recent Census 2021 data released by the Australian Statistics Bureau showed there are more than 122,000 people who are homeless in Australia and homelessness across the nation has risen by 5.2% between 2016 and 2021. Even worse, this data was collected before the current cost of living and housing crisis, which is pushing many into homelessness and is anticipated to result in an even greater need for support nationwide. 

From the 1st of May until the 1st of June, Ugg Express is donating 10% of all sales to Mission Australia which will go towards those who need it most. As well as this, on the 1st of June, for every purchase from the Wear Your Uggs Day collection, Ugg Express will be donating a pair of ugg boots to Mission Australia which will go to someone experiencing homelessness. 
If you are able to get involved please do 🫶🫶🫶
